Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Heavy rain showers over the weekend.
Clear- sunny day. No rain in last 9 days. Bottom temperature 57 F.
Partly sunny- some rain last couple mornings- windy (10 mph). Bottom temp 61 F.
Partly cloudy- thunderstorm last night. Windy (10-12 mph). Secchi reading taken when sun was out.  Bottom temp 67 F.
Partly sunny- no rain in last week. Wind ~ 5 mph. Hot last 4 days.  Bottom temp 70 F.
Sunny- rained twice in last week (~ 1.3 inches). Light wind- 70s for temp. More particulates in water than usual.  Bottom temp 63 F.
Partly cloudy w/ filtered sunshine- 12 mph wind- unseasonable cool temperatures for last 2 weeks.  Bottom temp. 56.3 F.
Partly sunny- 17 mph wind- below normal temp. / above normal precipitation over last month.  Bottom temp. 61.5 F.
Sunny- calm- much cooler than normal for last 3 weeks.  Precipitation normal.  Specks of green algae in water.
Sunny- calm- cool summer to date.  Water very clear and sparkling- pristine.
Calm- sunny- much cooler and very wet over last week.  Water very clear.  No specks in water.
Sunny- 5-7 mph wind- very cool last couple weeks.  Couple thunderstorms in last week.  Small amt particulate in water.
5 mph wind- sunny- little rain in last month.  Very clear water.
Sunny- 5 mph wind- ~ 70 F- warmer than normal Sept.- only 1 significant rain in last 2 1/2 weeks.  Bottom temp. 64.0 F.
sunny- 5-7 mph wind- water clear and sparkling- cooler and cloudier than normal for last month with little actual rain.
Partly cloudy- 65F 5-10mph wind- scattered thunderstorms last week.
partly cloudy- 75F- 5-10 mph winds- moderate boat activity- very windy with little rain this last week. (Temps upper 80's)
sunny- 5mph wind very warm and dry last 2 weeks
sunny- calm- 82F very hot and dry last three weeks- water very low- few small specks in water.

column1: Note: Water level is 11.25 inches down from mid-May when I put my dock in.

column2: sunny- 10mph winds- very warm and dry- water down 12.75" from mid May. Clouds of algae on bottom near shore.
sunny- 70F- calm- Approx. 1 inch rain last night- continued very dry in general- lake is 13.5" down from mid-May. Lots of algae clouds on bottom.
sunny- calm- been extremely dry- water down 15.75" from mid may- clouds of algae on bottom.
sunny- 70F- ~5mph wind- some rain last week- lake 16" down from mid-May- Algae clouds gone- very windy last few days.
sunny- 54F- 10-15mph wind- some floating green specks- temps below normal for May- water level up one inch from 4/26 level
sunny- 10 mph wind- lots of pollen in water and water doesn't have sparkling appearrance- water level 1/4" up from the 4/26 level
sunny- 78F- 5-7mph wind- water appears cloudy- not sparkling as in past years- water level now down 1" from 4/26 level
sunny- 5mph wind- very little rain in June (.87 inches)- water 4.5" down from 4/26 level (about 9.5" down from spring normal)
partly sunny- 72F- 5-7mph- extremely dry and very hot over last 6 weeks- small particulate in water- water level 7" down from 4/26 level and 12" from normal spring levels
partly sunny- 5mph- approx 7" rain over last week- water is 3.5" below 4/26 level- and about 8.5" below normal spring high- lots of fine particulate in water as well as many broken off weeds
partly sunny- 72F- 5 mph- heavy rain 2 weeks ago (~7") very little since- water is 6 inches below 4/26 level
Sunny- 65F- calm- been cool and dry for last week- 6.5" beloiw 4/26 level and 11.5" below normal spring high
sunny- 55F- 5 moh wind- about 2.5 inches rain in last week- lots of pollen on water near shore- water is 6.5" below 4/26 level
Sunny and calm. 65 degrees. Water level benchmark 10 inches.
Partly sunny. Lots of pollen in the water. Cooler the last couple of weeks. Water benchmark at 10.5 inches.
Sunny- 75 degrees. Wind 5-10 MPH. Water benchmark 10.5
Sunny. 82 degrees. Wind 5 to 10 MPH. Lots of algae specks in water. Water benchmark 12 inches.
Sunny- 69 degrees. Wind 5 MPH. Dry last week. Lots of algae specks in water. Water benchmark 13 inches.

Sunny- 75 degrees. Wind 5 to 10 MPH. Very hot and dry the last two weeks. No algae specks visible. Water benchmark 15 inches. Water clarity was at 10 feet for a few days and then declined. Sunny- 75 degrees. Wind 5 to 10 MPH. Very hot and dry the last two weeks. No algae specks visible. Water benchmark 15 inches. Water clarity was at 10 feet for a few days and then declined. August 10 - water benchmark 17 inches - lake level at about last years low.
Partly sunny- 70 degrees. Wind 5 to 10 MPH. Water benchmark 19 inches. No significant rain in 5 weeks. About 2 inches below last year's low water level.
Sunny- 68 degrees. Had about 1.5 inches of rain this last week. Water benchmark still at 19 inches- approaching 2005 low water level.
Sunny- first frost last night. No rain. Water benchmark now at 21 inches (lower than 2005- the lowest since we have been on the lake).

column1: September 22 - received 2.5 inches of rain Tuesday through Thursday - water benchmark now at 18.5 inches.

column2: Sunny- 5 MPH wind. No significant rain for 3.5 weeks. Water benchmark 11"
Partly sunny- 65 degrees. 51- 10 MPH wind. About 1.5 inches of rain in the last 6 weeks. Cool and damp with lots of wind. Water benchmark 12".
May 10- 2008 - Put dock in water. Water level benchmark set at 9 inches. About 2 inches of water flowing out of creek.

column1: July 7- 2008 - Parly sunny- 75 degrees. Calm. Water higher but not as clear as last three years. Water benchmark 11.5 inches. Summer much cooler than last year. 2 inches of rain in the last 10 days. Floating particulate in water.

column2: Sunny- 67 degrees. Calm. Lots of particulate in water. Water benchmark 11" - spring levels.
Sunny- 75 degrees. 10-15 MPH wind. Creek stopped flowing (lake outlet)- water benchmark 13 inches.
Sunny- 10 MPH wind. Water benchmark 18.5 inches. Water level getting low. No significant rain last 4 weeks. Above normal temperatures.
Sunny. 3-5 MPH wind. Cool and dry the last couple of weeks. Creek did not flow this spring. Water down 1 inch from dock in - about 10 inches below normal spring level.
Sunny and 73 degrees. 5 MPH wind. Cool and dry weather. About 11 inches below spring water level. Lots of pollen in the air.
Partly cloudy. 68 degrees. 10 MPH wind. Cool and dry. 16 inches below normal spring water levels.
Sunny and calm. 2.5 inches of rain last week. 16.5 inches below normal spring water levels.
Partly sunny. Calm and 72 degrees. 17.5 inches below normal spring water levels.

column1: September 17 - water is 18 inches below normal spring water levels. Lowest level since I have lived on the lake (10/2000).
October 2- 2009 - waer is 20 inches below normal spring water level.

column2: Sunny- 5-10 MPH wind- Hot and No Rail for Weeks- Water Benchmark = 14 3/4" (lower than last summer's low)
Partly Sunny- 5-10 MPH wind- About 7" rain in last 3 weeks- Waterbench Mark = 11"
Sunny- 75 degrees- 0-5 MPH wind- No significant rain in last week- Water Bench Mark = 11 1/2"
Sunny- 70 degrees- 0-5 MPH wid- Above normal rain for month- Water Benchmark = 11 1/2"- Cold nights last week
mostly sunny- 10-15 mph wind- water is colored- May has been cooler than normal with 5" rain to date - creek is flowing
sunny- 5 mph wind- heavy rain last week- cooler than normal June- creek running 2-3" deep- season about 2 weeks behind normal
sunny- 15 moh wind- warm with repeated showers last couple of weeks- creek still runnin 2-3" deep
sunny- 10 mph wind- much drier this last month- creek still runnin but only a trickle (stopped flowing Sept. 1st)
partly sunny- 10 mph wind- 65 degrees- lots of small algae flakes floating around- very ealry mspring creek flowing (only a trickle)
sunny- 5 mph wind- 65 degreesm 3.74" rain in June thus far- very windy month- creek still flowing- heavy LPB in bay
sunny- 80 degrees- 10-15 mph wind- heavy rains on July 2nd- 7th and 26th (2+")- very hot July- creek not running- bay secchi 9.5 heavy- LPB everywhere
sunny- 65 degrees- 10 mph wind- little rain in August- creek not runnin- LPB stopped growing and appears to be sinking to bottom
Partly cloudy. 65 degrees. Wind 0-5 MPH. Creek flowing. Cool spring. Ice out 5/1/2013.
Partly sunny. Calm. 76 degrees. Lots of pollen. Small clumps of large purple bladderwort floating around. Creek flowing.
Partly sunny. 68 degrees. Wind at 5 MPH. 5.5 inches of rain in June. Creek running. hot and dry last week. Large clumps of large purple bladderwort floating around.
Sunny and calm. 64 degrees. 2.74 inches of rain in July. Little large purple bladderwort floating in middle of lake- lots growing along shore on west side. Cool this last week.
Partly sunny. 70 degrees. Wind at 5-10 MPH. Creek dry. Very cold mid July through mid- August. Large purple bladderwort in south bay- boat launch- wildflower bay and northeast shore.
Sunny. 0-5 MPH wind. 60 degrees. Ice out 5/5. Creek running. Heavy tannin in water.
sunny; 0-5 MPH wind; 60F; ice out on 05/05/2014; creek running; heavy tannin present in water.
Sunny. 0-5 MPH wind. 71 degrees. Cool and cloudy the last few weeks. Creek running. June rain 6.73 inches. Lots of pollen in the water.
sunny; 0-5 mph wind; 71F; cool/cloudy over past few week; creek running; June rain: 6.73"; a lot of pollen and tannin in water
Sunny. 5 MPH wind. Large purple bladderwort just starting to emerge. Cooler than normal month. Creek running.
sunny; 5 mph wind; 75F; LPB just starting; cooler than normal month; creek running
Partly cloudy. 75 degrees. 8-10 MPH wind. Cool and wet summer. Creek running. LPB sinking. Water at spring level. Annual rainfall 5.11 inches above normal.
partly cloudy; 75F; 8-10 mph wind; cool and wet summer; creek running; LPB sinking; water similar to spring levels; yearly rainfall about 5.11" above normal
The day was sunny with about 5-10 mph of wind. I had Don Hoppe with me.
It was a little cloudy-winds 5-10 and clod around 57 degrees.
Mostly sunny with 5-10 mph of wind- Judy Penzenstadler helped with the observations.
calm sunny day 1-5 mph of wind
73 degrees sunny 10-15 mph winds Bob Meurer helped with observations.
partly sunny 5-10 mph bladderwort still visual.
68 degrees F- N wind 4 mph- very clear brown water- light rain showers last evening- very cold April- ice out 5-5-2018- 99.9" snow for winter. Chloride analysis 31.2 mg/L.
72 degrees- wind ESE 6 mph- mostly sunny- 6-7" of rain the past week- strong storms- visual pollen in water near shore

77 degrees- clear skies- 8 mph WNW wind- storms and wind over the last weekend dropped water temperatures from 82 to 74 (Friday to Monday) Bladderwort is in abundance over most of the lake. No noticeable algae. Lake AIS monitoring was done 7/23/2018 and NO invasive plant species were observed.

77 degrees F- westerly winds 13 mph- mostly sunny- no rain in the past three weeks- lake is 12" lower than in spring- bladderwort is present- large floating bog in south bay- pickerel weed is starting to grow in south bay- heavy motor boat use last weekend.

Record snowfall- 116" for season. 54 degrees- mostly sunny- SW winds 5 mph. Ice out was April 25th. Sample for Phosphorus and Chloride. Record snowfall- 116" for season. 54 degrees- mostly sunny- SW winds 5 mph. Ice out was April 25th. Sample for Phosphorus and Chloride.
65 degrees- partly cloudy- record rainfall this spring- cooler temperatures than normal- noticeable pollen in lake- virtually no boat traffic this past weekend.

73 degrees- NW wind 7 mph- sunny- major thunderstorms 19th + 20th- 2.5" rain- water temperature  74 degrees. Bladderwort is excessively present throughout the lake. Lake shore line is covered in "mats" up to 75 feet away from the shore.
Overcast skies- 57 degrees- wind is NE at 1 mph- surface water 67 degrees- bladderwort is still abundant- but beginning to sink to the bottom. Light boat traffic last weekend.
74 degrees- thunderstorms yesterday- NO chemistry/DO testing due to COVID-19 pandemic

65 degrees- NW wind 6 mph- sunny- noticeable pollen in lake- starting to see Bladderwort- moderate lake traffic last weekend ( 3 high powered ski boats + 4 jet skis on lake Saturday). Dissolved oxygen sampling not done due to COVID-19. Chloride was 343 mg/L
64 degrees- NW winds at 4 mph- clear day- humid- South Bay bladderwort accumulating in rafts/mats 15-30 feet from shore out into the lake

Our Loons hatched 2 chicks this year!!!! Only one made it- but how cool is that? It was 73 degrees- sunny with wsw winds at 13mph on the day of sampling. The lake was really busy this summer. I think people were escaping the Covid pandemic to a beautiful place. Bladder wort is dying out- less than last year.
